label: Getijden- en gebedenboek LTK 304

metadata.label: Title
metadata.value: Book of hours and prayers (Dutch, Latin), LTK 304

metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Contains: (ff. 1r-13v) Dutch calendar for Brussels. - (ff. 13v-14v) Latin gospel pericope (John 1,1-14) followed by a Dutch prayer to Christ. - (ff. 15r-49r) Hours of the Virgin. In Latin with rubrics in Dutch. - (ff. 50r-63r) Penitential psalms and Litany of all Saints. In Latin with rubric in Dutch - (f. 63r-v) Dutch prayer. - (ff. 64r-93r) Vigil. In Latin with rubric in Dutch - (ff. 93r-94v) Two Dutch prayers. - (ff. 95r-102v) Commendations. In Latin. - (ff. 103-214v) Various Dutch prayers. - Empty: ff. 49v.

metadata.label: Note
value: Binding: Post-medieval binding. - Rebound (1970): full leather over wooden boards; sewn on three supports; two clasp fastenings.

Textual: (ff. 15r-49r) Incipit: "Hier beghinnen die ghetijden van onser liever vrouwen te metten". - (ff. 103-214v) For the prayer on ff. 200v-202v, see Meertens (1930-1934), vol. 6, p. 30 sub 9. Also transmitted in German; communication Walter Röll, Trier (letter d.d. 17.12.1984). Incipit: "O almechtich ende ontfermhertich god ic bid u verleent mij ... ".
